&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT MUDDY MAT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Muddy Mat is a 9 figure revenue direct-to-consumer pet products brand, bootstrapped and profitable.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are the #1 selling indoor mat for cleaning dog paws, loved by millions of pet owners across America. Our portfolio includes Muddy Mat, Cloud K9 (anti-anxiety dog beds), and Wizz (pet stain remover).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We operate across Direct Response TV, direct-to-consumer e-commerce, Amazon, TikTok Shop, and expanding retail partnerships with major chains including Home Depot, Costco, and Walmart. With 95-98% of sales in the US, and soon to be more international.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a real CFO seat at a high-growth, nimble, profitable business,&lt;strong&gt; not a reporting role buried under layers of corporate bureaucracy.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE OPPORTUNITY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a hands-on, strategic CFO to own the entire finance function, lead a team of 4 (two bookkeepers, one auditor, one controller), and prepare the business for a raise. You will report directly to the Founder/CEO and have full P&amp;amp;L visibility and ownership.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires someone who can operate at 30,000 feet (strategy, capital markets, exit prep) and at ground level (ERP cleanup, cost optimization, hands-on problem solving). We are a lean organization that values truth, ownership, and results over corporate theater.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Finance &amp;amp; Exit Readiness&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead preparation for capital raise or strategic exit, including data room creation, CIM support, and buyer/investor Q&amp;amp;A&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage Quality of Earnings (QoE) process and due diligence with investment banks, PE firms, and strategic acquirers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain relationships with banks, lenders, and capital partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop 12-24 month financial forecasts and scenario models for growth planning and exit valuation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own capital allocation strategy and provide recommendations on investment priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Financial Operations &amp;amp; Systems&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clean up and optimize Fulfil.io ERP system, chart of accounts, inventory costing, revenue recognition&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure timely and accurate monthly, quarterly, and annual close processes&lt;/li&gt;
